It is not clear whether President Fernández wants to remain in politics when her term ends, given that she no longer has her husband by her side.
If he does, he will need the support of the middle class, much of which has grown tired of kirchnerism.
When the Argentines return from their summer holidays in March, the wave of sympathy for her will have fallen.
If you want to win another election, you will have to decide whether or not you repudiate, with tranquility, many of your husband’s policies.
