“You have two options: you can contact the players in the sector and tell them: we’re going to negotiate a satisfactory agreement with a good price.”
"However, the idea is that what matters is not the price, but the people's competition," Laporte said.
The contract awarded to the Énergie gérance consortium is part of a long list of contracts of more than $50,000 obtained by the Quebec Party.
The contracts were awarded by Hydro-Québec or SEBJ for the Eastmain-1-A-Sarcelle-Rupert project.
