This is the second obstacle identified by the Barometer, after the higher price of these products.
In addition, one-third of Quebecers say they also distrust the supposed yields of the ecological products or services they are trying to sell.
On the other hand, nearly half of consumers changed their habits in 2010 and, especially, changed the brand of one or more products to respect their beliefs.
61% have given priority to shopping in their neighborhood’s shops and have preferred to buy food products grown in their region, the Barometer notes.
