Clotilde Reiss: The Elysée has exaggerated Syria's mediation
For more than ten months, between July 2009 and May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, the young French investigator detained in Iran for "espionage", has haunted the public in France, has alerted to diplomacy and has accentuated the deterioration of relations between Paris and Tehran.
